Wash and dry produce. Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Cut @broccoli{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Halve @mandarin orange{2}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Place green beans and @butter{1%tablespoon} in a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}; cover with #plastic wrap{} and microwave until tender, ~{2-3%minutes} (continue to microwave in 30-second intervals if needed). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}; toss to combine.

Open package of @chopped chicken breast{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid.

Add a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} to a hot #large pan{}. Add chicken, broccoli, salt and pepper; cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is cooked through and broccoli is tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, whisk @apricot jam{1%unit}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, half the @soy sauce{1%tablespoon}, half the @cornstarch{1%tablespoon}, 1 tsp @rice wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, and juice from orange halves.

> Be sure to measure the vinegar—we sent more!

To pan with chicken and broccoli, add orange-soy mixture and scallion whites; cook, stirring, until sauce has thickened and everything is coated, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

While sauce cooks, massage @microwaveable jasmine rice{1%unit} in package; snip to partially open. Microwave until tender, ~{90%seconds}. Fluff and season with salt and pepper.

Top rice with chicken and broccoli and green beans (draining first). Sprinkle with scallion greens and @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon}. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.